1.3. The 'So What?' for the Business

This Inventory Intelligence function provides a defensive shield, giving operations and finance leaders the preemptive insights needed to protect the bottom line. By constantly scanning for these two types of problems, it delivers two primary benefits:

* Prevents Lost Sales: By catching stockout risks, it ensures the business doesn't miss out on revenue from customers who are ready to buy.
* Reduces Wasted Capital: By identifying overstock, it frees up money that would otherwise be tied up in products sitting on a shelf.

While Inventory Intelligence protects the business from losing money, the second job, Revenue Amplification, actively seeks out new ways to make more money.


